title: Nassiba Laghouati
text:
Nassiba Laghouati (; born 23 January 1976) is an Algerian <a href="women%27s%20association%20football">football</a> former player and current <a href="Manager%20%28association%20football%29">manager</a>. She played as a <a href="midfielder">midfielder</a> and has been a member of the <a href="Algeria%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Algeria women's national team</a>.
Club career.
Laghouati has played for ASE Alger Centre and Affak Relizane in Algeria. She has been <a href="player-coach">player-coach</a> in the latter.
International career.
Laghouati capped for Algeria at senior level during the <a href="2006%20African%20Women%27s%20Championship">2006 African Women's Championship</a>.
